sp.
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Renier" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[1248,1429,747,773]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chaetopteridae" genus="Chaetopterus" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="variopedatus">
cf. 
<emphasis box="[1283,1429,747,773]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">variopedatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, usually in male-female pairs in each tube (
<bibRefCitation author="Haig J." box="[626,748,783,809]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" pagination="171 - 192" refId="ref72846" refString="Haig J. (1962) Papers from Dr. Th. Mortensen's Pacific Expedition 1914 - 1916. 79. Porcellanid crabs from eastern and western America. Videnskabelige meddelelser fra Dansk naturhistorisk forening i KjObenhavn, 124, 171 - 192." type="journal article" year="1962">Haig 1962</bibRefCitation>
; present study, see 
<figureCitation box="[963,1046,783,809]" captionStart="FIGURE 81" captionStartId="129.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-19@129.[179,1407,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="129" captionText="FIGURE 81. Polyonyx nitidus Lockington, 1878: A, male (cl 7.5 mm, cw 10.0 mm) from Las Perlas Islands, Panama (MZUSP 33661), in chaetopterid worm tube (host removed); B, ovigerous female (cl 9.2 mm, cw 13.2 mm) from the same locality (MZUSP 33661), dorsal view [photographs by AA]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5532410/files/figure.png" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Fig. 81</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="127" pageNumber="128" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="127.[151,1437,386,1241]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,819,845]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[324,463,819,846]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" pagination="1 - 440" refId="ref72816" refString="Haig, J. (1960) The Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Anomura) of the Eastern Pacific. Allan Hancock Pacific Expedition, 24, 1 - 440." type="journal article" year="1960">Haig (1960)</bibRefCitation>
treated 
<taxonomicName authority="Glassell, 1935" authorityName="Glassell" authorityYear="1935" box="[557,944,819,846]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Polyonyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadriungulatus">
<emphasis box="[557,772,819,845]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">P. quadriungulatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Glassell, S. A." box="[781,944,819,846]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" pagination="91 - 106" refId="ref71820" refString="Glassell, S. A. (1935) New or little known crabs from the Pacific coast of northern Mexico. Transactions of the San Diego Society of Natural History, 8, 91 - 106." type="journal article" year="1935">Glassell, 1935</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from the warm-temperate outer Baja California as a species morphologically distinct from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lockington" authorityYear="1878" box="[706,810,855,881]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Polyonyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidus">
<emphasis box="[706,810,855,881]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">P. nitidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, supposed to occur in the Gulf of California and further south along the Pacific coast to 
<collectingCountry box="[514,609,891,917]" name="Ecuador" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, including the 
<collectingRegion box="[778,987,891,917]" country="Ecuador" name="Galapagos" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Galápagos Islands</collectingRegion>
. She was aware that the differences between these two presumed species were rather slight, suggesting that they may also be considered as subspecies of a single species. Werding (2001) concluded that the characters used by 
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[925,1060,963,990]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" pagination="1 - 440" refId="ref72816" refString="Haig, J. (1960) The Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Anomura) of the Eastern Pacific. Allan Hancock Pacific Expedition, 24, 1 - 440." type="journal article" year="1960">Haig (1960)</bibRefCitation>
to distinguish 
<taxonomicName box="[1224,1436,963,989]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Polyonyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadriangulatus">
<emphasis box="[1224,1436,963,989]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">P. quadriangulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lockington" authorityYear="1878" box="[201,306,999,1025]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Polyonyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidus">
<emphasis box="[201,306,999,1025]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">P. nitidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(number and configuration of movable spinules on the propodi and number of fixed spines on the dactyli of P2–P4) are not consistent, and that therefore 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Glassell" authorityYear="1935" box="[781,995,1035,1061]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Polyonyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadriungulatus">
<emphasis box="[781,995,1035,1061]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">P. quadriungulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be treated as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lockington" authorityYear="1878" box="[181,285,1071,1097]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Polyonyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidus">
<emphasis box="[181,285,1071,1097]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">P. nitidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Hiller, A. &amp; Lazarus, J. F. &amp; Werding, B." box="[395,591,1071,1097]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" refId="ref73488" refString="Hiller, A., Lazarus, J. F. &amp; Werding, B. (2004) New records and range extensions for porcellanid crabs in the eastern Pacific (Crustacea: Anomura: Porcellanidae). In: Hendrickx, M. E. (Ed.), Contributions to the Study of East Pacific Crustaceans. Vol. 3. Instituto de Ciencias del Mar y Limnologia, Universidad de Mexico / UNAM, Ciudad de Mexico, pp. 1 - 12." type="book" year="2004">
Hiller 
<emphasis box="[467,523,1071,1097]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">et al.</emphasis>
2004
</bibRefCitation>
). Indeed, in the present Panamanian material, the number of spinules on the ventral surface of the P2–P4 propodi varied from four to six: two to four medially aligned spinules and two spinules on the distal corner, near the propodo-dactylar articulation. The uniform pale orange-brown colouration of the Panamanian specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lockington" authorityYear="1878" box="[397,502,1179,1205]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Polyonyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidus">
<emphasis box="[397,502,1179,1205]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">P. nitidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[518,613,1179,1205]" captionStart="FIGURE 80" captionStartId="128.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-19@128.[179,1407,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="128" captionText="FIGURE 80. Polyonyx nitidus Lockington, 1878: A–C, male (cl 7.5 mm, cw 10.0 mm) from Las Perlas Islands, Panama (MZUSP 33661), dorsal (A), ventral (B) and frontal (C) views [photographs by AA]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5532408/files/figure.png" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Figs. 80</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[626,655,1179,1205]" captionStart="FIGURE 81" captionStartId="129.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-19@129.[179,1407,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="129" captionText="FIGURE 81. Polyonyx nitidus Lockington, 1878: A, male (cl 7.5 mm, cw 10.0 mm) from Las Perlas Islands, Panama (MZUSP 33661), in chaetopterid worm tube (host removed); B, ovigerous female (cl 9.2 mm, cw 13.2 mm) from the same locality (MZUSP 33661), dorsal view [photographs by AA]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5532410/files/figure.png" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">81</figureCitation>
) corresponds well to that of the 
<collectingRegion box="[1023,1141,1179,1205]" country="Ecuador" name="Galapagos" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Galápagos</collectingRegion>
specimens in 
<bibRefCitation author="Hickman, C. P. &amp; Zimmerman, T. L." pageId="127" pageNumber="128" refId="ref73387" refString="Hickman, C. P. &amp; Zimmerman, T. L. (2000) A field guide to crustaceans of Galapagos: an illustrated guidebook to the common barnacles, shrimps, lobsters and crabs of the Galapagos Islands. Sugar Spring Press, Lexington, 156 pp." type="book" year="2000">Hickman &amp; Zimmerman (2000)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="127.[151,567,1323,1350]" box="[151,567,1323,1350]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,567,1323,1350]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Lamarck, 1801" authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1801" box="[238,567,1323,1350]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Porcellana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,370,1323,1350]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Porcellana</emphasis>
Lamarck, 1801
